The paper deals with the problem of computing ruling sets in graphs, which is a fundamental problem in distributed algorithms. This suggests that the paper belongs to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also involves techniques of randomized sparsification, which is a common technique in the Design and Analysis of Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. The paper deals with graph algorithms, which is a common topic in the Algorithms (cs.AL) sub-category. The paper involves network algorithms, which is a common topic in the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves graph theory, which is a common topic in the Graph Theory (cs.GT) sub-category.
